xtra semester to pay for, I don&#8217;t think there will be cheering then. Life sometimes teaches us hard lessons.</p></div><div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="https://reason.com/wp-login.php?redirect_to=https%3A%2F%2Freason.com%2F2020%2F04%2F13%2Fcoronavirus-parenting-school-covid-19-learning%2F">Log in to Reply <i class="fas fa-reply"></i></a></div></div></li><li class="comment byuser odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-8208378" data-sort-time="1586861856"><div id="div-comment-8208378" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>anitafox</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2020/04/13/coronavirus-parenting-school-covid-19-learning/#comment-8208378">April.14.2020 at 6:57 am </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>Hello from Phoenix<br /> I am a painting teacher in elementary grades and it’s clear that we are quarantined now. I understand the seriousness of the situation and try not to leave home for no reason. It’s good that working as an academic writer on the Paperell (<a href="https://paperell.com/" rel="nofollow ugc">https://paperell.com/</a>) not only helps me not lose my mind, but also provides myself normally in this difficult time. The main thing is to panic less, treat hands and products. Everything will be fine.</p></div><div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="https://reason.com/wp-login.php?redirect_to=https%3A%2F%2Freason.com%2F2020%2F04%2F13%2Fcoronavirus-parenting-school-covid-19-learning%2F">Log in to Reply <i class="fas fa-reply"></i></a></div></div></li><li class="comment byuser even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-8208931" data-sort-time="1586880352"><div id="div-comment-8208931" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>NJ2AZ</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2020/04/13/coronavi